name: Alex Gladstein üåã ‚ö°
tweet: 21/ In the process of writing this book, I have learned an enormous amount about the power of money, and how, sadly, it is used as a tool of control and repression around the world.  I have also learned that Bitcoin provides hope for a freer future ‚úåÔ∏è

name: Alex Gladstein üåã ‚ö°
tweet: 20/ Bitcoin‚Äôs rising use in El Salvador, Togo, Senegal, Cuba, Palestine, and Afghanistan; Bitcoin as an antidote to monetary colonialism; Bitcoin‚Äôs humanitarian and environmental impact; Bitcoin as an American ideal; and, finally, Bitcoin as a potential new world reserve currency

name: Alex Gladstein üåã ‚ö°
tweet: 19/ These chapters cover the personal stories of Bitcoin users in Nigeria, Sudan, and Ethiopia; Bitcoin‚Äôs pre-history and the cypherpunk movement; Bitcoin in comparison to the negative externalities of the dollar system; Bitcoin‚Äôs Trojan Horse mechanism of adoption...

name: Alex Gladstein üåã ‚ö°
tweet: 18/ @BitcoinMagazine gave me the space to write these pages that aim to contextualize Bitcoin adoption alongside economic and political history.

name: Alex Gladstein üåã ‚ö°
tweet: 17/ This book is a collection of writing done throughout 2020 and 2021 as I explored the global impact of Bitcoin, and tried to report on what financial privilege too often obscures.

name: Alex Gladstein üåã ‚ö°
tweet: 16/ The Bitcoin protocol does not care about your level of wealth, color of your skin, beliefs, family history, religion, or nationality.  It is neutral and cannot discriminate.

name: Alex Gladstein üåã ‚ö°
tweet: 14/ Financial privilege is embedded in our world, and has steered the course of history.  It has shifted power from the have-nots to the haves.  It is getting worse.  But guess what?  Bitcoin is going to obliterate financial privilege.
